      <p>The average U.S. side hustle earns <a href="https://due.com/make-money-online/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$530/month</a>, though the median is closer to $200. Beginners in affiliate marketing earn $0&ndash;$1,000/month in year one, with most earning under $300 in months 1&ndash;6. Virtual assistants start at $15&ndash;$25/hour. Website testers earn $30&ndash;$300/month. The long-term gap is significant: <a href="https://www.postaffiliatepro.com/blog/how-much-can-beginner-make-affiliate-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">affiliates with 3+ years earn 9.45&times; more</a> than those with less than one year.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Why do most beginners fail to earn money online?</summary>
